    • lazyDelete

      public void lazyDelete(E e)
      This method simply changes a flag variable in a node, marking it as unusable and removing it from the active usable nodes, effectively deleting it but not removing its data. It doesn't return anything
      Parameters:
      e - The given node to mark as deleted

    • trimTree

      public void trimTree()
      Recursive method. It traverses a tree and removes every node marked as unusable but not actually having been deleted yet. Acts on a given binary tree

    • findElement

      public boolean findElement(E e)
      This method traverses a given binary tree to search for a specific element. It simply returns true or false if found or not.
      Parameters:
      e - Element to be found
      Returns:
      boolean True if the element is found and usable, false if otherwise
